  "notes": "Muscogee / Creek (Mvskoke) — Muskogean language of Oklahoma, written in the Latin script with the traditional Creek alphabet. Two orthographic conventions deserve note: ⟨c⟩ = /tʃ/ and ⟨r⟩ = the voiceless lateral fricative /ɬ/ (not a rhotic). ⟨v⟩ is the short central vowel /ə ~ a/ and ⟨ē⟩ the long /iː/. Vowel length and pitch accent are phonemic; length is only partly written. This spec covers the traditional (Loughridge/Bible) alphabet, which remains the community standard.",
